%N A394365 The number of squares visited by a knight moving on a square-spiral numbered board, starting from square n, and always moving to the lowest available unvisited square while never crossing the path of any previous step (Cf. A394363), or -1 if no such number exists.
%C A394365 There are three starting squares, n = 8, 43, 112, that lead to the path being infinite; see A394364 and A394363 for more information and images.
%C A394365 The first path to have the longest finite length before being trapped after the first step to a larger square than the previous one is for start square 340, which visits 6 squares moving toward the central 1 square before visiting a further 99 squares before being trapped. See the attached image.
%H A394365 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A394365/b394365.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A394365 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A394365/a394365.png">Image of the path for a(340) = 105</a>. The start and end squares are colored green and red respectively, while the 8 squares around the final square that the knight is blocked from stepping to are colored blue.
%e A394365 a(1) = 37. See A394363.
%e A394365 a(8) = -1. See A394364.
%e A394365 a(340) = 105. See the attached image.
%Y A394365 Cf. A394363, A394364 (end squares), A316667, A336208, A383185.
%K A394365 sign,walk
%O A394365 1,1
